Title: Studio Journal: Watercolor Moisture Control
Date: 2026-06-19
Source: mira_019_studio_journal.pdf
Demo Persona: Mira Vale
Privacy Level: private

Had a challenging session with watercolors, trying to paint a soft gradient. The paper buckled because I used too much water. I waited for it to dry, pressed it flat, and tried again with drier brush techniques. Learning to control paper moisture is a slow but satisfying skill.